 Urumi is set in the backdrop of the fierce     
 warrior clans of Northern Kerala in the        
 sixteenth century and focuses on the cult of   
 Chirakkal Kelu a man with an epic mission. His 
 target and mission is Dom Vasco da Gama,       
 the Viceroy of Portuguese Empire in India.     
 The film is spread between the second and      
 third visit of Gama to India and chronicles    
 a varied version of how Gama could have met    
 a bloody death in AD 1524. In the journey      
 of Kelu, he has to encounter the seamless      
 conflicts within the kinsmen and also kings,   
